a, K., Brown, V.K., Berg, M.P., Wardle, D.A., Wall, D.H., Trophic interactions in a changing world: Modelling aboveground- belowground interactions (2004) Basic Appl. Ecol., 5, pp. 515-528; Shaver, G.R., Jonasson, S., Response of arctic ecosystems to climate change: Results of long-term field experiments in Sweden and Alaska (1999) Polar Res., 18, pp. 245-252; (2000) Bryophyte Biology., , Shaw, A. J. Goffinet, B. (ed.). Cambridge University Press, Cambridge, UK; Smith, E.M., Coherence of microbial respiration rate and cell-specific bacterial activity in a coastal planktonic community (1998) Aquat. Microb. Ecol., 16, pp. 27-35; Sommerkorn, M., Bölter, M., Kappen, L., Carbon dioxide fluxes of soils and mosses in wet tundra of Taimyr Peninsula, Siberia: Controlling factors and contribution to net system fluxes (1999) Polar Res., 18, pp. 253-260; Swanson, R.V., Flanagan, L.B., Environmental regulation of carbon dioxide exchange at the forest floor in a boreal black spruce ecosystem (2001) Agr. Forest Meteorol., 108, pp. 165-181; Ullrich, S., Karrasch, B., Hoppe, H.-G., Is the CTC dye technique an adequate approach for estimating active bacterial cells? (1999) Aquat. Microb. Ecol., 17, pp. 207-209; Walker, D.A., Walker, M.D., Terrain and vegetation of the Imnavait Creek watershed (1996) Landscape Function and Disturbance in Arctic Tundra., pp. 73-108. , In: Reynolds, J. F. Tenhunen, J. D. (ed.), Springer, Berlin. p; Wilson, J.A., Coxson, D.S., Carbon flux in a subalpine spruce-fir forest: Pulse release from Hylocomium splendens feather-moss mats (1999) Can. J. Bot., 77, pp. 564-569; Wolters, V., Silver, W.L., Bignell, D.E., Coleman, D.C., Lavelle, P., Van Der Putten, W.H., De Ruiter, P., Van Veen, J.A., Effects of global changes on above- and belowground biodiversity in terrestrial ecosystems: Implications for ecosystem functioning (2000) Bioscience, 50, pp. 1089-1098","Roger Anderson, O.; Department of Biology, Lamont-Doherty Earth Observatory of Columbia University, Pa